xinhua news agency , beijing , march 25 , a spokesman for the south korean presidential office announced on the 25 th in seoul that south korean president kim dae - jung 's special adviser for foreign affairs and security unification , lin dong - yuan , will visit north korea in the first week of april . he will hold talks with north korean officials on the exchange of visits by separated families and how to ease the tense relations between the south and the north of the korean peninsula .
the spokesman said : the dprk side hopes that the talks will " lay a foundation " for the resumption of south - north relations , but she did not mention the specific situation of the talks .
she said that the talks would be announced after the return of lin dong - yuan from north korea .
at the same time , the dprk central news agency also issued a brief statement on the same day , saying that president kim dae - jung 's special envoy will visit the dprk .
the statement said that the two sides will hold talks on the " serious situation " on the korean peninsula and issues of common concern .
indonesian parliament speaker on trial
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 25 , according to information received here , the indonesian parliament speaker akbar tanjung appeared at a court in jakarta on the 25 th on charges of corruption and redemption .
tanjung was accused of being responsible for the illegal embezzlement of $ 3.8 million worth of relief funds from the indonesian state food and food bureau .
it was reported that the funds were later used to finance the 1999 election campaign of the professional group led by tanjung .
these relief funds were originally used to provide some poor families affected by the financial crisis , but the investigators found that the funds were not in the hands of these families .
however , tanjung has denied the above charges .
analysts believe that no matter what the outcome of the trial is , this incident may weaken the hope that tanjung will be elected president of indonesia .
" forging ahead " postponed to space due to mechanical failure
xinhua news agency , washington , march 25 , the us national space agency said on the 25 th that due to technical problems in the canadian - made mechanical hands in the international space station , the launch of the " forging ahead " space shuttle will be postponed from may 6 to may 31 .
it is reported that the " forging ahead " will carry seven astronauts to the international space station for a 11 - day space flight .
these seven people include astronauts from france and russia .
a spokesman for the us national aviation and space agency said that the space station staff could take advantage of this sufficient time to remove the trouble , but the delay of the launch also means that they would have to patiently stay for three weeks and wait for the us pelosi and two other russian astronauts to replace them .
philippe perry , from france , is the first non - russian european astronaut to fly to the space station . he will walk in space two times at the beginning of the mission .
shell 's investment in china to reach 5 billion us dollars in three years
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 26 ( reporter qian chunxian ) the chairman of the shell group , wu zipei , said a few days ago that by 2005 , shell 's total investment in china will reach us $ 5 billion .
at the china development forum held here , he said shell 's investment in china has reached 1.6 billion us dollars , and some of the projects under planning will reach 5 billion us dollars in 2005 .
shell is currently negotiating with the chinese side on a number of cooperative projects .
among them , a joint venture with the china petrochemical corporation to set up 500 gas stations in jiangsu is expected to start this year .
he said shell has had business contacts with china for more than 100 years .
as far as shell is concerned , china has huge market potential and is an important part of its global strategy .
with the development of the economy , china 's energy demand is expected to double by 2020 , and by that time , china 's energy consumption will account for 16 percent of the world 's total .
china is facing severe energy challenges , and the diversification of energy sources is very important to energy safety and environmental protection , and shell will play an important role in this process .
xinhua news agency , united nations , march 26 ( reporter gu zhenqiu ) a un security council spokesman announced on the 26 th that the un security council delegation will visit the congo ( kinshasa ) and other african countries involved in the conflicts in the congo ( drc ) on april 27 , so as to inject new vitality into the peace process in the congo ( drc ) .
the spokesman said that the french permanent representative to the united nations lewis will be the head of the delegation and the delegation will be composed of representatives from 15 un security council members .
the main purpose of the visit is to hold dialogue with the leaders of all parties involved in the conflicts in the congo ( drc ) in order to promote the compliance of the peace accord signed by the parties in zambia 's capital of lusaka in 1999 .
this is the third time that the un security council has sent a delegation to visit the great lakes region of africa since may 2000 .
sri lanka to hold peace talks with tigers
xinhua news agency , colombo , march 27 ( reporter zhang yadong ) the sri lankan government announced on the 27th that it plans to hold peace talks with the rebel liberation tigers of tamil eelam in early may in order to end the nearly 20 - year - long bloody national conflicts in the country .
at a press conference held on the same day , the minister of justice , constitution , racial affairs , and national unity of sri lanka said that the sri lankan government and the tigers have agreed to hold peace talks as soon as possible , and the government hopes that the talks will be held in the first week of may .
he said : the initial talks will mainly make preparations for entering the substantive talks .
the slovak government has not yet officially announced the venue of the talks , but it has been reported that the peace talks between the two sides will be held in thailand .
pelosi said that the government plans to hold talks with the tigers in a certain asian country and has made relevant preparations for this .
according to another report , after three years of exile in london , the chief negotiator of the tigers in the northern part of sri lanka who had returned to the region under the control of the tigers on the 25 th , as well as the leader of the organization , pu abalam , recently held talks with the norwegian special envoy to the republic of sri lanka , the norwegian ambassador to slovakia , and so on .
after the talks , the tigers agreed to resume peace talks with the government when the regional situation under their control was restored to normal , but still insisted that the government lift the ban on them before the peace talks .
in february this year , the sri lankan government and the tigers signed a permanent ceasefire agreement , laying a foundation for the start of the talks between the two sides .
last year , china unicom 's net profit rose nearly 38%
xinhua news agency , hong kong , march 27 ( reporter li kai ) the china united telecommunications corporation , which is listed in hong kong , announced here today that in 2001 , china unicom has achieved good results in various business , with a total turnover of 29.393 billion yuan rmb and a net profit of 44.57 billion yuan , an increase of nearly 38% over the previous year .
as one of china 's comprehensive telecommunications operators , china unicom provides a variety of telecommunications services , including mobile communications , international and domestic long - distance , data , internet , and paging services .
china united telecommunications corporation announced that last year , the company 's long - distance telephone and e - phone service was 64.1 billion minutes , an increase of 5.9 times over the previous year , and its market share increased from 1.3 percent in 2000 to 7.7 percent , and the total international time for the whole year was 3.4 times more than the previous year .
yang xianzu , chief executive officer of china united telecommunications corporation , said that this year , the company will continue to speed up the development of mobile communications business and adopt a different strategy to ensure the coordinated development of the mobile communications business of the company , which will continue to increase the number of mobile phone users of the company .
china , japan sign currency exchange agreement
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 28 ( reporter wang yan ) dai xianglong , governor of the people 's bank of china , and masaru hayami , governor of the bank of japan , signed a bilateral currency exchange agreement between the renminbi and the japanese yen in tokyo on the 28th .
according to the agreement , the people 's bank of china and the bank of japan can provide each other with a total of $ 3 billion worth of currency exchange arrangements to help maintain the stability of the financial market .
the signing of the currency exchange agreement between china and japan shows that the cooperation between the central banks of china and japan has been further strengthened .
the agreement is the second bilateral currency exchange agreement signed between the people 's bank of china and the bank of thailand in december 2001 .
in the future , china will also sign currency exchange agreements with the rok and some other countries .
dai xianglong said : china will actively participate in asian financial cooperation and is willing to work together with other asian countries and regions to make contributions to regional economic and financial stability and prevention of risks .
wu dawei , chinese ambassador to japan , attended the signing ceremony of the currency exchange agreement between the people 's bank of china and the bank of japan .
earthquake victims start rebuilding homes in afghanistan
xinhua news agency , kabul , march 28 ( reporter pan yunzhao ) just three days after the earthquake , earthquake victims in the northern afghan province of baghdad have begun rebuilding their homes .
the spokesman of the united nations humanitarian aid coordination office in afghanistan , libeka , told xinhua reporters that a central group formed by the afghan interim government , un organizations , and non - governmental organizations , during an inspection and assessment of the earthquake - stricken areas on the 28th , found that the disaster victims had already started rebuilding their own houses , and some of them also used relief materials provided by relief organizations to the disaster victims .
she said that based on this situation , the un rescue agency has begun to consider the issue of helping the disaster victims rebuild their homes .
at present , relief organizations have already had a large amount of relief supplies in the earthquake - stricken areas , and are being distributed to disaster victims through both ground and air means .
a strong earthquake measuring 5.1 on the richter scale has killed and injured tens of thousands of people , according to reports reaching here today .
japan temporarily freeze humanitarian aid to russia
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 29 , japanese foreign minister kawaguchi announced on the 29 th that japan will temporarily freeze humanitarian aid to russia until the japanese side has rectified the international committee responsible for the aid projects .
kawaguchi said that in addition to maintaining the commission 's human expenditure and a technical cooperation project currently provided by japan to russia , the japanese government will control the funding assistance provided to russia by the committee until it is rectified .
the move was made in response to the recent remarks made by japanese finance minister masaru hayami .
the cabinet members should ensure that every fund of the government can be used in the light of the continued deterioration of japan 's financial situation .
it has been learned that the committee has been criticized by the outside world for dereliction of duty and the lack of transparency on the issue of the flow of funds after the deputy chief cabinet secretary takeo hiranuma put pressure on the ministry of foreign affairs and affected the application procedures for russian aid projects .
eu to hold talks with china on measures to safeguard steel imports
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 29 , shi guangsheng , minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation , said here today that the eu has made a clear response to china 's concern about the eu 's temporary safeguard measures for some steel imports , and that it will hold consultations with the chinese side as soon as possible and make some special arrangements for china as a developing country to properly resolve this issue .
shi guangsheng answered reporters ' questions at a national foreign economic and trade legal work conference today .
he said : at present , the increasingly fierce trade war between steel products comes from the united states .
at present , all parties concerned are making accusations against the " 201 steel case " of the united states and their requests for bilateral consultations , and some have even proposed to resolve the issue through the wto dispute resolution mechanism .
on 27 march , after the eu decided to implement temporary safeguard measures against 15 kinds of steel imports from various countries , the chinese side made a timely response . shi guangsheng immediately sent a letter to eu trade commissioner lamy to express deep concern over this and proposed bilateral consultations with the eu .
seven killed in train collision in liaoning
xinhua news agency , shenyang , march 30 ( reporter wang jun ) at 14 : 13 on march 29 , a train - car collision accident took place in jinhua city , liaoning province , killing seven people and seriously injuring three .
according to a briefing by the safety inspection office of the shenyang railway bureau , a four - wheel agricultural vehicle collided with a train from jinzhou to chengde at a railway crossing between li jiagou and zhou jiadun in jinzhou city 's yixian county .
at that time , apart from carrying 50 bags of fertilizer and seeds , the car also carried 14 people in violation of regulations .
at the time of the collision , four people jumped out of the car to escape , and there were no injuries . the remaining 10 people were either killed or injured , the blocking of the railway , and the train train was damaged to a certain extent .
after the accident , leaders of the ministry of railways , the shenyang railway bureau , the jinzhou city railway bureau , and the local government rushed to the scene to deal with the aftermath of the accident .
the arab league council held an emergency meeting at the arab league headquarters on the same day to discuss the situation in palestine .
twenty - two arab countries ' permanent representatives attended the meeting .
at a press conference after the meeting , moussa said that israel 's escalation of military action against palestine clearly shows that israel refuses peace .
what is happening now is a continuation of israel 's military occupation of palestine , and the palestinian people will continue to resist israel 's aggression .
he said : " as long as israel 's military occupation of palestinian territories exists , as long as israeli tanks and soldiers exist in palestinian territories , the resistance of the palestinian people will continue for one day . "
xinhua news agency , jerusalem , march 31 ( reporter zhong cuihua and nie xiaoyang ) - the israeli security cabinet decided on the evening of the 31 st to step up military strikes against the palestinian - controlled areas and put into effect a series of planned military actions ahead of schedule .
on the afternoon of the same day , israeli prime minister sharon convened a meeting of the core ministers to discuss the current situation between israel and palestine and how to deal with the increasingly frequent bombing attacks on the palestinian side , and the meeting decided to step up military strikes against the palestinian side .
political figures here have revealed that the security cabinet believes that intensifying the crackdown on the palestinian side will weaken the momentum of palestinian terrorist activities , but it is impossible to fundamentally stop such attacks .
