the protocol stipulates that the georgian troops will withdraw from the mountain valley in cote d'ivoire by april 10 , while the peacekeeping forces and un observers will resume their patrols in the region , and all parties concerned should ensure the safety of the residents in the region .
the special representative of the un secretary general to georgia , boding , believes that this protocol is a " good signal , " indicating that georgia and abkhaz are willing to resolve the conflict on the basis of mutual compromise .
he said : this document should open up a way for further dialogue .
in 1992 , the abkhaz local authorities in georgia had armed conflicts with the georgian government because of their demand for independence .
in october last year , the two sides once again clashed with each other in the mountains , and georgia immediately sent troops to the area .
