another sandstorms hit north china and other places .
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 6 ( reporter dong jun ) the central meteorological station announced at 6 : 00 p.m . today that under the influence of strong cold air , there will be sand and dust weather in the eastern part of the northwest , most parts of north china , and the central and southern part of the northeast plain from tonight to tomorrow .
it is predicted that there will be sandstorms in some areas in the central and eastern provinces of inner mongolia , the northern part of shaanxi , shanxi , and hebei , and the western part of liaoning and jilin provinces , and there will be strong dust or sand storms in some areas of the huang he and huai he . the temperature in the above - mentioned areas will drop by 6 to 12 degrees celsius , and the temperature in some areas will exceed 14 degrees celsius .
this morning , the city of beijing was sunny , but in the afternoon it started to stir up a strong wind , driving people who were engaged in outdoor activities home one after another .
although the central meteorological station released a forecast of strong winds in north china and other places yesterday evening , the weather has attracted many residents to take advantage of the early days of the spring rain .
today , the capital of inner mongolia autonomous region , hugh , also experienced a strong wind and cool weather .
although the north wind is blowing , the sky is still very clear .
experts said that the spring rain fell in inner mongolia yesterday , and the rainfall in the city was 33 millimetres , which not only greatly alleviated the drought , but also effectively curbed the attack of sand storms .
by 2005 , china 's telecommunications market will exceed 1 trillion yuan
xinhua news agency , shanghai , april 6 ( reporter feng yizhen ) an official from the ministry of information industry , who is attending a high - level seminar on information and communications between china and russia , revealed that by 2005 , the total volume of china 's telecommunications market will reach 1050 billion yuan , an increase of 2.5 times over 2000 .
it is estimated that during the 10th five - year plan period ( 2001 - 2005 ) , the number of telephone users in china will increase at an average annual rate of about 26 percent , with 24 percent in the central and eastern regions , 26 percent in the central region , and 30 percent in the western region .
by 2005 , the number of telephone users nationwide will reach 500 million , and the popularization rate will be about 40 percent .
china 's mobile phone users will expand to ordinary consumers , and will expand from simple news service to data exchange , medium - and high - speed multimedia and high - speed interactive multimedia business .
the internet business will continue to be the fastest growing business in china 's communications industry , and the contents of demand will extend from the narrow range to the broadband business , the development of the classified broadcast business to the high - speed interactive business , and the expansion of users from large and medium - sized cities to central cities and towns .
during the 10th five - year plan period , the average annual growth rate of china 's data and multimedia internet users will exceed 70 percent .
by 2005 , the number of internet users nationwide will reach 200 million .
