east timor 's presidential campaign ends
xinhua news agency , jakarta , april 12 , the three - week presidential election in east timor ended today .
voters will elect the first president of the country to be officially independent on may 20 .
the candidates participating in the presidential election included samara gusmao and shavarar .
gusmao was the leader of the east timor independence movement , and the president of the " democratic republic of east timor " was announced in november 1975 .
the two candidates held an open debate on the 11 th and answered questions raised by the voters .
gusmao said that after his election , he would first work to resolve the country 's economic problems and that the country 's democracy would be guaranteed .
public opinion generally believes that gusmao is likely to win , because he is considered a hero in east timor who has won independence .
under the auspices of the united nations , east timor held a referendum on 30 august 1999 , with the overwhelming majority of voters choosing independence .
on august 30 last year , east timor officially elected a constitutional assembly and adopted the first constitution of the country in march this year .
the new constitution will take effect on 20 may when east timor is officially independent , and the constitutional assembly will become the first national assembly .
