( detailed report ) chavez re - becomes venezuelan president
xinhua news agency , caracas , april 14 ( reporter jia anping ) venezuelan president chavez , who was detained by the coup military two days ago , returned to the presidential palace on the 14th and was sworn in as president of the republic of venezuela , amid the cheers of supporters .
in his televised speech to the whole country , chavez thanked the venezuelan people for their trust and support for him , thanked the organization of american states , the rio group , the group of 77 , and other international organizations for safeguarding democracy and condemning the coup , and called on all circles in venezuela to take reconciliation action .
chavez stressed that venezuela needs peace , stability , and reason , and that all parties concerned should make joint efforts to stop the conflict .
he said : through this incident , " we have learned many things , and we will strive to correct our past mistakes and mistakes and jointly build our country . "
on the 11 th , a military coup took place in venezuela , and more than 10 senior military officers declared that they would not support the chavez government and detained chavez .
carmona , former chairman of the venezuelan entrepreneurs association , took up the post of interim president of the interim government on the 12th .
on the same day , the masses supporting chavez held a peaceful demonstration in the capital and demanded that chavez take power again .
on the afternoon of the 13 th , a group of pro - chavez military protection vice president camilla returned to the presidential palace and was sworn in as interim president on the evening of the 13 th . carmona announced his resignation .
the army that supported chavez then issued an ultimatum to the coup military to release chavez and occupy the important strategic base in the military camp .
on the early morning of the 14 th , chavez returned to the presidential palace from the detained caribbean island by helicopter .
