first round of voting for french presidential election
xinhua news agency , paris , april 21 ( reporter liang guihe ) the first round of voting for the french presidential election started at 8:00 a.m . on the 21st at 640,000 polling stations nationwide in france .
among the 16 candidates , 40 million voters will elect the seventh president of the fifth republic of france .
the results of the voting were announced on the evening of the same day .
according to a press release issued by the french interior ministry , the voter turnout rate was 21.41 percent at noon on the 21 st , down from 22.52 percent in the first round of voting in the 1995 presidential election .
according to local media forecasts , the turnout rate this year may be the lowest in history .
the french constitution stipulates that if no candidate wins more than 51 percent of the votes in the first round of voting , the two candidates with the highest votes will enter the second round of competition on may 5 .
the results of the last public opinion poll released last friday showed that incumbent president chirac and incumbent prime minister lionel jospin might win with a very close number of votes in the first round .
since there are as many as 16 candidates in the presidential election , the highest record in french history , the voting may be very scattered in the first round of voting .
the french far - right national front presidential candidate leponte may be the third in the first round of voting , and may even become the " cold door " to enter the first two .
