( london - us united microelectronics ) the british government is committed to resolving the increasingly serious street crime problem and will deploy more police to patrol .
interior minister brundtland said it is very necessary to curb the rising street robbery and violence and increase police patrols .
he said : " we should indeed rectify the order on the streets , because law - abiding citizens hope to walk safely on the streets and live a safe life , and there is no need to fear that they will be attacked . "
despite the decline in the overall crime rate in britain , the number of street crimes increased by 13 percent from 2000 to 2001 .
the situation in london is even more shocking , and the number of robbery cases reported in september and november 2001 alone was 10,298 , more than double the figure of 8,614 in the same period of the previous year .
the government also said that the increase in crimes was mainly due to the large increase in the number of mobile phones , and more than 700,000 mobile phone robberies occurred throughout the country last year .
this is the first time that the british police have focused their crackdown on street hooligans and robbery , and in the past , they have concentrated their efforts on the illegal possession of guns and the sale of drugs on the streets .
the new plan will first be implemented in 10 streets where crimes are more concentrated .
police will step up patrols in these streets and provide more protection to victims .
