global warming once again warns of the complete collapse of the antarctic ice cap
( auckland comprehensive ) experts from the us national ice and snow data center said yesterday that the antarctic has completely broken down and split into several thousand ice mountains , and this is the largest of these incidents in the past 30 years , thus issuing another warning on the issue of global warming .
it has been learned that a section of the larson b ice , with an area of 3,250 square kilometers , near the eastern coast of the south pole island , has been completely destroyed in 35 days .
the center warned that with the arrival of the hot summer , other ice towers are also on the brink of collapse .
this indicates that the flow of the ice river in the southern hemisphere will increase , the global sea level will rise , and this will cause harm to the low - lying areas .
the center , located at the university of colorado , said on its website ( nidc . org ) that it might have been 10,000 tons in 2000 and 720 billion tons of ice , which started to split up on january 31 this year , and the ice has formed several thousand floating ice mountains in the weidan sea .
the center also said that the reason for the split of the ice cap was the regional climate warming .
